"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-27-im-honoured-celine-dion-relishes-comeback-performance-at-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Grammy-winning Canadian singer, Celine Dion has relished her first performance in four years which was at the 2024 Olympic Games opening ceremony in Paris, France, on Friday.  The 56-year-old ailing singer performed 'Hymne \\u00e0 l'amour' by the French singer, \\u00c9dith Piaf from the base of the Eiffel Tower in what was an instantly iconic moment.  Dion, who has not performed publicly since 2020 amid her battle with stiff-person's syndrome, released a statement to relish her iconic performance at the 2024 Paris Olympics.  \\\"I am honored to have performed tonight, for the Paris 2024 Opening Ceremony, and so full of joy to be back in one of my very favorite cities!,\\\" she said.  \\\"Most of all, I am so happy to be celebrating these amazing athletes, with all their stories of sacrifice and determination, pain and perseverance.  \\\"All of you have been so focused on your dream, and whether or not you take home a medal, I hope that being here means that it has come true for you!  \\\"You should all be so proud, we know how hard you have worked to be the best of the best. Stay focused, keep going, my heart is with you!\\\" She wrote.  This is Dion's second performance at the Olympic Games.  She performed at the Atlanta 1996 Olympic Games.  According to TMZ, Dion was paid for her performance at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.  DAILY POST recalls that Celine Dion had vowed that she would not let her Stiff Person Syndrome battle stop her from performing again.  In an interview with Hoda Kotb on the Today Show, she vowed that she would resume live performances even if she had to crawl to the stage and talk with her hands.  Beyonc\\u00e9 introduces Team USA at 2024 Paris Olympics  'Dating no longer fun' - BBNaija Vee  I do not know Celine Dion - Arsenal star, Bukayo Saka  NNPP chieftain decries Nigeria's performance at Paris Olympic  Paris Olympics: It's quite disheartening - Chioma Ajunwa bemoans Nigeria's outing  US Election: I did not permit Trump to use my song for his campaign - Celine Dion clarifies  'I will be remembered for my classics even if I stop singing' - Celine Dion  Celine Dion performs at 2024 Paris Olympics amid health battle [VIDEO]  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"